30/11/2007
ATHENS, Greece -- Police smashed an international ring that trafficked women for sex, arresting 30 people in Athens and Thessaloniki in a wide-ranging operation Thursday (November 29th).
Conducted with the help of Interpol and Europol, it involved more than 200 policemen.
In all, 30 people were arrested, and three victims -- two Russians and a Romanian woman -- were released.
Police are searching for more than 20 other suspects believed to be part of the network.
In other news Thursday, the Greek government announced it is drafting a bill aimed at stopping illegal trafficking in antiquities.
In part, it envisions appointing a special prosecutor to handle such cases.
(ANA-MPA, AP, AFP - 29/11/07)
